The paper focuses on user response prediction in online advertising and recommendation systems, which involves learning feature interactions from high-dimensional sparse features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV).
